  "title": "NDT Level 3",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description & Requirements</strong></p><p>ASNT NDT Level III, PCN NDT Level III,\nAdvanced NDT Specialist</p><p>Familiarisation of ASME & API Codes\n& Standards</p><p>Ability to assume full technical\nresponsibility for clients’ NDT facilities.</p><p>Proven experience of providing solutions to\nclients’ NDT inspection related problems.</p><p>Maintain all of equipment and consumable\nstorage in the store room to be ready for using with good conditions under\nacceptance criteria specific by client or international standard.</p><p>Willingness to be flexible and multi-task\nas part of a team, and contribute to company objectives.</p><p>Strongly motivated to achieve results, with\na high degree of professionalism, honesty and integrity.</p><p>Excellent organizational and time\nmanagement skills, able to priorities workloads with competing deadlines.</p><p>Good written skills to produce coursework\nand training materials, as well as clients’ NDT procedures, written practices,\ntechniques and audit reports.</p><p>Provide internal trainiand technical\nguidance for other inspectors</p><p>Ensure that all personal certification is\nkept up to date.</p><p>Develop and approve NDT procedures, written\npractices and NDT techniques to a high standard that comply with clients</p><p>Creative skills to plan and deliver lessons\nin a professional, positive and engaging manner.</p><p>Ensure adequate training and cross checking\nthe site works, share knowledgewith team members and contribute to team\ndevelopment.</p><p>To analyse work plans and projects, and as\nwell as recommendations of every working unit; and to give advice on safety\nmeasures to the employer.</p><p>Feedback on revised Equipment’s and\nsoftware’s for improvement.</p><p>Feedback after testing the new equipment on\nsite for improvement.</p><p>Extensive knowledge of own subject area\nwith extensive industrial NDT experience holding multiple NDT method Level III\ncertification ASNT (RT,PT,UT,MT,VT,ET) /CSWIP (PAUT/TOFD)</p><p>Preferable:</p><p>Master's degree in NDT</p><p>Bachelor degree in Mechanical Engineering</p>",
